		<SectionTitle Id="ResponsiveLayout" />
		<p>
			To achieve responsiveness of the sidebar (such as this documentation site has) you need to adjust application layout.
			The main layout might look like:
		</p>
		<CodeSnippet File="~\Pages\Components\HxSidebarDoc\HxSidebar_Layout.CodeSnippet.razor" />
		<DocAlert Type="DocAlertType.Warning">
			If you are using standard Blazor application template, you need to remove all the unnecessary CSS rules from <code>site.css</code>.
		</DocAlert>
		<p>You don't need any other layout-related CSS in <code>site.css</code>:</p>
		<CodeSnippet File="~\Pages\Components\HxSidebarDoc\HxSidebar_Setup.CodeSnippet.css" />

		<SectionTitle Id="expand-collapse">Expand & collapse programmatically</SectionTitle>
		<p>Bind the <code>Collapsed</code> parameter to track whether the sidebar is collapsed and to expand or collapse the sidebar.</p>
		<Demo Type="typeof(HxSidebar_Demo_ProgramaticallyExpandCollapse)" />
	</MainContent>
